# Cursor AI Rules for LockerRoom Development

## Terminology Standards

**CRITICAL**: All user-facing text MUST use "Academy" and "Player" terminology, NOT "School" and "Student".

### Rules:
1. **UI Components**: Always use "Academy" and "Player" in:
   - Labels, placeholders, error messages, success messages
   - Toast notifications, page titles, table headers
   - Form fields, button labels, dialog descriptions

2. **Code Variables**: May use "school" and "student" for:
   - Variable names, API endpoints, database queries
   - Type definitions (for backend compatibility)

3. **Role Display**: Always use `getRoleDisplayName()` from `@/lib/role-display` when displaying user roles.

### Examples:
- ✅ `<Label>Academy Name</Label>`
- ✅ `toast({ title: "Player Added Successfully" })`
- ✅ `<span>{getRoleDisplayName(user.role)}</span>`
- ❌ `<Label>School Name</Label>`
- ❌ `toast({ title: "Student Added" })`

### Reference:
- See `DEVELOPER_GUIDELINES.md` for complete standards
- See `client/src/lib/role-display.ts` for role display utility

